 Well I would say there are a few things you could do:

(1) Contact the inspector and ask if they waived the past fail or the initial inspector was incorrect;

(2) Contact a local real estate attorney who gives free consultations who can tell you yes/no as to whether there is a code; 

(3) Contact the Condo Board and inquire of any of them has dealt with the code requirements you've encountered. 

I wouldn't pay them until you get a clear answer. Who knows what occurred and it's better to get to the bottom of it now, instead of later.
